abstract: Representative Adam Schiff, the lead House manager, said the notes “in many respects are more important than the manuscript.”
snippet: Representative Adam Schiff, the lead House manager, said the notes “in many respects are more important than the manuscript.”
lead_paragraph: Democrats don’t just want to hear from John R. Bolton, President Trump’s former national security adviser. They also want his notes — and getting them could help pave the way for other documents they have been demanding.
headline_main: Democrats want to hear from Bolton, but they also want his notes.

abstract: Abuse of power and obstruction of Congress have long been considered criminal and merit impeachment.
snippet: Abuse of power and obstruction of Congress have long been considered criminal and merit impeachment.
lead_paragraph: Watching CNN last week, I learned that I’m partly responsible for President Trump’s legal defense.

abstract: Lawyers representing U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial launch a second day of defense arguments on Monday as the proceedings on whether to remove him from office enter a critical week.
snippet: Lawyers representing U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial launch a second day of defense arguments on Monday as the proceedings on whether to remove him from office enter a critical week.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Lawyers representing U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial launch a second day of defense arguments on Monday as the proceedings on whether to remove him from office enter a critical week.

abstract: Mr. Bolton’s political action committee has given away more than $1 million, some of it to senators who are now considering whether to subpoena him.
snippet: Mr. Bolton’s political action committee has given away more than $1 million, some of it to senators who are now considering whether to subpoena him.
lead_paragraph: John R. Bolton was President Trump’s national security adviser for a year and a half, but he has been a fixture in conservative politics for a generation, making it difficult for Republicans to merely dismiss him as a partisan with an ax to grind. There is no better evidence of the complications his potential testimony would create for Senate Republicans than the campaign checks he has written many of them.
headline_main: For Republican senators, Bolton brings an added pressure point: money.

abstract: A lonely voice in favor of calling Mr. Bolton believes he may soon have more company.
snippet: A lonely voice in favor of calling Mr. Bolton believes he may soon have more company.
lead_paragraph: For weeks, Senator Mitt Romney, Republican of Utah, has been the only Republican senator openly supportive of calling John R. Bolton, the former White House national security adviser, to testify in President Trump’s impeachment trial.
headline_main: Romney says it is ‘increasingly likely’ the Senate will call Bolton.

abstract: Prominent attorney Alan Dershowitz and two former independent counsels, Ken Starr and Robert Ray, will be among those defending President Donald Trump when they make their case to the U.S. Senate on Monday.
snippet: Prominent attorney Alan Dershowitz and two former independent counsels, Ken Starr and Robert Ray, will be among those defending President Donald Trump when they make their case to the U.S. Senate on Monday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Prominent attorney Alan Dershowitz and two former independent counsels, Ken Starr and Robert Ray, will be among those defending President Donald Trump when they make their case to the U.S. Senate on Monday.

abstract: President Donald Trump's impeachment trial may not result in his removal from office, but it could help determine whether his Republicans retain control of the Senate in the November congressional elections.
snippet: President Donald Trump's impeachment trial may not result in his removal from office, but it could help determine whether his Republicans retain control of the Senate in the November congressional elections.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump's impeachment trial may not result in his removal from office, but it could help determine whether his Republicans retain control of the Senate in the November congressional elections.
headline_main: There's Something Else at Stake in Trump Impeachment: Control of U.S. Senate
headline_print_headline: There's Something Else at Stake in Trump Impeachment: Control of U.S. Senate

abstract: President Donald Trump told his then-national security adviser in August that he wanted to continue freezing $391 million in security aid to Ukraine until officials there helped with investigations into Democrats, including presidential rival Joe Biden, the New York Times reported on Sunday.
snippet: President Donald Trump told his then-national security adviser in August that he wanted to continue freezing $391 million in security aid to Ukraine until officials there helped with investigations into Democrats, including presidential rival Joe ...

abstract: President Hassan Rouhani said on Monday Iran should stick to rules set by an anti-money laundering watchdog to protect ties between the sanctions-hit country and international banks, as a deadline for compliance looms.

lead_paragraph: DUBAI — President Hassan Rouhani said on Monday Iran should stick to rules set by an anti-money laundering watchdog to protect ties between the sanctions-hit country and international banks, as a deadline for compliance looms.
headline_main: Rouhani Urges Anti-Money Laundering Compliance to Curb Iran Isolation
headline_print_headline: Rouhani Urges Anti-Money Laundering Compliance to Curb Iran Isolation
